caption: Food was good after picking out all the chicken from a specifically vegetarian dish. Would expect more for a spot that claims vegan and gluten-free
Food is Great!!!

I ordered a lot of takeout during my trip to Chicago (the only option due to COVID rules) and this place by far had the BEST ordering experience. They clearly labeled all their allergens, made adding/subtracting ingredients straightforward, and clearly presented all their menu options. The online order process has replaced the “ambiance” of eating, and this place nailed it. The food itself was great too—good portion size, freshness, and flavors.

I love love love Brightwok!!! It's our go to restaurant. They have the yummiest bowls! The veggies are really fresh and the bowls have a good ratio of veggies and protein. Really healthy, flavorsome and so many options! I really like their sauces too.

Best food! Best service! Best everything! I love Brightwok and the staff so much! The food is always so fresh and delicious! We spend a lot of money here and it’s always been well worth it. The staff greets us EVERY time we enter and they are always so kind and helpful and easy going with any request I need. One thing I’m absolutely most grateful for is this is the one and only place in the entire city I can honestly say has never, not once messed up my food. That’s a common problem I have with take out, but Brightwok is perfect 100% of the time.

Delicious food, but their ventilation is awful. You can expect to leave this place with your clothes smelling aggressively like the cooking oil/smoke. They need to fix this, and until then, I will not return. The value for the portion/quality is also not so great.
Good, clean food. A great option for River North fast casual. I switch between here and Sweetgreen.
Thank you for such a delicious lunch!

One of the best healthy food places that I ate in Chicago. Staff is super nice, location is very convenient and the portions are great, and you can simply eat there every day because the food is healthy and tasty. Tried the "everyday eat right" and the sweet umami mushroom" so far and looking forward to try the rest of their plates

3/23/2020 Just ordered, picked up and enjoyed Brightwok Kitchen’s meals. All three of us really enjoyed the heck out of the meal.  We picked up our “to go” meals, walked seven blocks on a cold day, reached the condo and enjoyed the delicious meals.  Packaging was perfect for transporting as the food stayed warm.  Will definitely be enjoying Brightwok Kitchen more often. Great pricing too.

Not a satisfying interpretation of Asian cuisine. Could not finish the dish due to disappointment, which was a shame as it was pricey.  It lingered in the fridge until being unceremoniously discarded.
Being from out of town we went on a few recomendations, and we were not disappointed at all! Kid friendly, very delicious!
$10, a massive bowl of actually hot curry stir fry. I also can't believe it was so empty on a night for dinner. And make sure you try the ginger beer, not too sharp and a light sweetness.

This is a good lunch spot with a lot of healthy options. It's something a bit different in the neighborhood and a good addition. I get take out from here somewhat regularly and have never been disappointed. My only complaint is it's a bit pricey for lunch but I'm sure their rent is crazy expensive and it seems like they use fresh ingredients.
They do a good job, always taste good. I get food there every other week.

As someone with Celiac disease, I often struggle to find restaurants where I can safely eat more than a couple items on the menu. At Brightwok, I can eat everything, which absolutely blew my mind the first time I came. Every experience I have had here has been nothing short of incredible. The food is always great and the portion sizes are more than adequate, they offer a student discount, and the staff is always super friendly and helpful. Hands down one of my favorite places to eat in all of Chicago.
I certainly loved the food and service, good location very close to my house. The cashiers are always very nice. Will come visit again.

Brightwok Kitchen is our favorite place when we want a quick, healthy meal. All the ingredients are fresh and the dishes are prepared with great care. I've been there several times and I've never been disappointed. Thanks, Brightwok!
Good service. Food doesn't taste so good. Greasy and overcooked.
Super quick, fresh ingredients. Helpful and friendly staff!
Delicious food, but no cash allowed.

(Translated by Google) The atmosphere is quiet and there are a lot of seats to take out and I've seen a lot of takeouts ~~ Eateveryday eat right + sweet potato: Personally it was so hot ... I kept pulling water ... earth, curry and fire have eggs on it but only the eggs are delicious ... others are just okay..a little bit of spicy curry. If you want to eat dinner or dinner, why don't you stop by? (I'll just eat ..) I'll be satisfied once I go!  (Original) 📎분위기는 조용하고 앉을자리는 많은편, 테이크아웃도 많이 해가는 모습을 보았어요~~ 📎everyday eat right + sweet potato: 개인적으로 너무 짰어요... 계속 물이 당기더라고요... earth, curry and fire 는 계란이 올라가져 있는건데 계란만 맛있고...다른건 그냥 무난한..조금 사알짝 매운카레맛정도가 다였어요.. 📎바로 만들어주니까 저녁이나 밥하기 귀찮다 싶을때 들리시면 좋을지도요? (저는 그냥 밥해먹을게요..) 한번 간 것으로 만족할게요!

(Translated by Google) Im healthy. Everything is really a good restaurant and a welcome restaurant for vegetarians, only one big problem. No taste. 5 jeomim for someone healthy to eat.  (Original) 건강식임. 모든 게 정말 좋은 식당이고 베지테리안이라면 환영할 만한 식당인데 단 하나의 큰 문제점. 맛이 없음. 건강하게 먹을 사람에겐 5점임.
I love the food just too high $10 unless a promotion is going on.
Quick, good ingredients, and delicious. I very much enjoyed the Earth, curry, and fire, it's actually spicy.
100% gluten free ingredients, fresh and flavorful, beautiful looseleaf teas, lovely decor
Awesome restaurant
Great

Best spot for a filling healthy warm meal. ENTIRELY GLUTEN FREE, and vegan friendly! Friendly, warm, wonderful staff (don't forget to tip!). The Magic Cakes and Loaded Potato Fritters are to die for! Enjoy

This is not an asian cuisine. It’s something else, all the food I’ve tried in Thailand and other asian countries are another level of quality. The tofu tastes awful and the tea quality is very poor - everything is overpriced for its taste and quality.  It says tea with turmeric and ginger - and I got a tea from the package that tastes nothing like turmeric or ginger. Just a usual cheap black tea....

I've been coming here since the week it opened, but I'll have to reconsider options the next time I think about quick Asian. As with most places in Chicago, it's become inconsistent, wrong orders, (3 of the last four times) they have changed recipes and how they cook orders and preparations to ruin the great thing they had going.  If you order your make your own bowl, they will make it how they like it anyway so beware.  The Adams location is better as I've been to both often. Beware the teriyaki sauce they put on what it seems like everything now without telling you it ruins everything.

Tasty hot wok bowls prepared fresh to order. You can choose one from four that are listed on the menu (chicken, steak, or tofu - plus a selection of veggies, served with white or brown rice or rice noodles) or make your own bowl with the sauce, base, protein and four veggies of your choice.  Two cold salads on the menu - one with chicken, one with tofu. Vegan and vegetarian friendly.  I had the Earth, Curry and Fire and my mouth sure was on fire afterwards - but in a good way. Delicious!

Reasonably priced, large portions and friendly service. We both got the Thai basil bowl. I mentioned that I didn’t want chicken in my bowl and they were able to sub 2 additional vegetables instead which was perfect! Would definitely go back.
Good
Very yummy and fast!
Omg this place is amazing. Only place you need to know for quick, healthy, and delicious stir fry in Chicago. All about the sauce.
Good music vibes and celiac friendly!
Good stir fry, similar set up like Chipotle. Make sure you customize your order, and ask about extras.
I ordered delivery from here. It's delicious yet a bit pricey for a Thai fast-food. I guess it's popular because of offering many gluten free options (which was not important to me).
Love this place so much it gives me butterflies. Go there on an average 2-3 times a week with an occasional week break. SO good, without the guilt. Also staff is so sweet!

Everything is gluten free and dairy free and all the sauces were vegan (the sauces on offer may change seasonally, so be sure to check). I built a Thai Curry bowl and it was an EXPLOSION of flavor. I added the sweet potato fritter and that was delicious too. So good, highly recommended!
Pretty healthy at a good price. Small menu, but consistently executed.

The service and the food were excellent!  I ordered the dish with brown rice, broccoli, onions, carrots, green peppers.  It was cooked to perfection, nice flavors throughout the meal.  I tried the magic cake was delicious but my only complaint was the piece of cake was rather small.  Otherwise, I will be back.
Loved it.. great value!
Excellent tasty food! Huge plus is that you can minus plus anything in the item you like.

Very nice fast casual restaurant offering simple Asian fusion bowls. Chicken, beef and veggie options and make your own as well. Very tasty. You can adjust the spiciness to your liking. Noisy and a bit smokey from the Wok cooking oil.
The food is good and healthy and the staff is very kind and excellent in service

Not a big fan of asian cuisine, but I was surprised by the quality of ingredients and the good taste of this food. I got there very close to closing time, they were nice enough to prepare a Healhy Sesame for me. What could be worse than a Seven Eleven salad, right? Let’s see what the deal with this small restaurant. That was a good decision. At the end they  asked me how food was, pretty impresive at $9. I even received a $2 coupon for me to use it next time. Thank you.
Fast service. Friendly helpful staff. Amazing options for the bowls and even more amazing taste. Super clean inside and easy to find. Definitely recommend!
A great place for a quick, healthy meal. Choose your items and create a stir fry bowl Chipotle-style. They often mix up the orders, so make sure you leave with what you purchased!
Delicious and filling. Highly recommend
Very fresh flavorful food. Must try in Chicago
Great food and service, always relatively quick.
Food was awesome!
They were so full (I was a walk-in), I had to sit at the bar (with rap music). The food was good, so I see why people like it. :)
great flavors and really helpful employees
Food was great. Service was nice. Clean restaurant including the bathroom. Soup was not the best..
Ate at both locations just to try them out. I've been to both numerous times and have yet to be disappointed. Check out the sweet potato hash, highly recommended.
Brightwok is an amazing place! Completely gluten free menu, everything they waste is compostable. Good food, good heart, great company.
I usually don’t frequent such hipster establishments, but this place is worth the condescension.

I noticed it was around the corner from my hotel and I checked it out, did not disappoint at all. Restaurant was super clean, staff was extremely friendly, especially Jeremy, and on top of that the food is delicious!
Sooo freaking good!! Please come to the suburbs!
Healthy and warm food served fast.  Update: been here 5+ times and this time the bowl had wayyyy too much sauce. It was so salty that I had to throw half of the bowl away.

Very fresh food cooked to order. Was impressed that someone came around to the tables to ask us how our meals tasted. Felt like that was above and beyond what would be expected from a dining experience without servers waiting on us. I would highly recommend the place. Also if you like food on the spicier side they can really put a good kick in there for you.

5+ plus for Brightwok. They do a heck of a job at this spot. High quality ingredients, served hot and at a good price point. Brightwok is quick as well, so it's a great go-to in the area. Their menu can get expensive if you aren't paying attention, but there are a lot of options in the $10-$12 range, which is so reasonable for lunch and dinner. I would highly recommend checking out this fast casual spot!  They are also super okay with customizing anything!
Pretty good food, and friendly staff. But the music is way, way, WAY TOO LOUD!
Great new spot in River North! Great good and very clean! Will be in the rotation for a lunch spot!
Great atmosphere

A nice new lunch spot! Food was a little expensive, but on-par for the area and they definitely don't skimp. The cashew bowl and the summer jalapeno bowl were both delicious, and you could also make your own creation. Fresh and healthy food. There's also a siracha dispenser which is awesome, and they take NFC payments.

Great new addition to river north, perfect for lunch break from work or for tourists. Pretty fast service. Nice bright design. Would love to see an order in advance system like sweet green. Bonus takes Apple Pay !
